<TEXT>
harold leland goodwin a prolific author who 
wrote science adventure books for youngsters and books about space 
exploration for general readers has died he was 75 
goodwin who wrote under the pseudonym john blaine died of 
cardiac arrest at his bethesda md home sunday 
goodwin worked at various times for nasa and the national 
oceanic and atmospheric administration 
his largest enterprise was the 26volume rick brant science 
adventure series for youngsters the first book rockets 
shadow was published in 1947 and the most recent the magic 
talisman came out this year 
</TEXT>
