<DOCNO> AP900221-0007 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
opening a hotel is never easy but launching the 
first westernmanaged hotel in poland taxed the creativity of 
veteran marriott corp executives 
reaching a jointventure agreement for the warsaw marriott was 
just the start next was the problem of furnishing and equipping 
the 41story 520room hotel built in the shell of a dormant 
warsaw skyscraper 
just about everything was imported said marriott spokesman 
gordon lambourne 
then there was the matter of finding local employees with the 
proper attitude 
the sense of hospitality the sense of private enterprise 
doesnt exist said william r tiefel president of marriotts 
hotels division theres not much incentive to be very creative 
in a job 
the most difficult task was securing a reliable supply of food 
and drink for the hotels 11 restaurants and bars you dont shop 
for prime rib and fine wine in a country where shoppers queue for 
bread and potatoes 
marriotts problems reflect the difficulties inherent in 
cultivating capitalism in old staterun economies its not a 
matter of adding a little water and fertilizer you have to plant 
the very seeds 
marriott took the challenge literally it signed contracts with 
polish farmers fishermen and a brewery to ensure a moreorless 
steady stream of local provisions ranging from beer to lettuce 
it even imported the seed used by the farmers so the produce 
would be up to its standards 
in addition marriott built a freezing and canning plant to 
ensure a yearround supply along with huge food lockers and 
storage areas to hold a months worth of goods much of it imported 
the hotel opened in october and the company is pleased enough 
that its considering outposts in other major east bloc cities 
including budapest prague and moscow 
marriott is no stranger to opening hotels in nonwestern 
countries it had to negotiate similar food procurement contracts 
in the middle east and barbados tiefel said 
but the warsaw hotel posed the most difficult problems the 
company ever faced he said 
the idea for the hotel the first uspolish joint venture 
since the end of american economic sanctions against poland in 
1987 began four years ago when marriott was contacted by partners 
in its vienna hotel tiefel said 
the parters ilbau the austrian construction company that 
built the hotel and girozentrale the bank that financed it 
joined with lot the polish governmentowned airline in proposing 
the warsaw hotel they wanted marriott to run it 
under the joint venture marriott holds an approximate 25 
percent interest in ownership and operation of the hotel and the 
office space that occupies 20 of the buildings floors it also 
gets an undisclosed percentage of profits 
the hotels rooms are rented for foreign currency only and the 
polish government gets a cut the restaurants and bars accept 
zlotys the polish currency which are used to pay most hotel 
expenses 
as for staffing tiefel said there was not a work force to 
draw on that had experience in the lodging business so the 
criteria changed the bigger the smile the quicker we hired 
them he said 
marriott brought in 25 managers to school the staff in 
addition it trained 22 polish workers in the united states and 
brought in several dozen housekeepers bartenders and other 
employees from its western hotels to work alongside their polish 
counterparts tiefel said 
samir daqqaq the hotels marketing director said western 
managers in poland need a very deep well of patience you dont 
train just once it is an ongoing process 
the employees are given two meals daily partly to reduce food 
theft in addition to wages slightly above what they would get 
elsewhere in poland the pay is adjusted monthly for the nations 
runaway inflation marriott said but perhaps the most prized perks 
are the hotel uniforms 
one bellman we have these really nice bellmans uniforms 
he postponed his wedding so he could wear it on his wedding day 
lambourne said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

