more than a week after it was 
discovered the body of a 15ton whale that washed ashore still lay 
on the beach while officials decided which province would remove it 
the whale washed ashore about nine days ago at elomeid about 55 
miles west of this mediterranean city but had not been removed by 
tuesday because officials in alexandria claimed the halfburied 
carcass was not in their province but in that of mersa matruh 
mersa matruh is unequipped to deal with the body of such a large 
animal which rarely appears in egypts mediterranean waters the 
last time a dead whale was washed ashore in egypt was in 1936 said 
sherif ramadan at the oceanography institute 
an official at alexandrias fire department said that if mersa 
matruh asked for help it would send firefighters with cranes along 
with butchers to cut up the whales body which was so 
disintegrated it could not be lifted whole 
