at least one federal agency is among the ranks 
of deadbeats who dont pay their taxes on time adding as much as 
250 million to the total of taxes owed but not turned over to the 
internal revenue service 
in fact irs officials hint that several federal agencies 
delayed handing over withheld taxes at one time or another 
prompting rep byron l dorgan dnd to complain such actions 
carry the definition of a tax deadbeat to a new low 
if the irs cant make a federal agency own up to its tax 
responsibility who can they influence dorgan said tuesday after 
a hearing by the house ways and means oversight subcommittee on 
taxes owed but not collected the total of those 13 million 
accounts receivable is rising by 11 million a day to as high as 
87 billion 
dorgan said members of the subcommittee have information that 
one federal agency was late in turning over more than 250 million 
it had withheld from workers paychecks 
irs commissioner fred t goldberg jr acknowledged only that one 
agency which he would not identify because of privacy laws was 
once listed among taxpayers with a delinquency of 100 million or 
more 
