the maiden voyage of czechoslovakias new 
reformist government to the united states was a symbolic 
fullcircle return to values long cherished by czechs and slovaks 
but also an exciting personal experience for members of the 
delegation 
when president vaclav havel shook president bushs hand inside 
the white house it was a beginning of a new era a strong reminder 
of 1918 when woodrow wilson played a key role in establishing free 
czechoslovakia and an overwhelming victory for havel a former 
dissident playwright 
havel the first president in czechoslovak history to visit 
washington with full honors of a head of state still remembers the 
