the telephone network as a success story but acknowledged that 
callers too often get busy signals 
the telephone network which went nationwide last october was 
expected to handle about 250000 calls a day but more than 15 
million people try to get through on peak days and many of them 
call between 10 am and 2 pm she said 
the 800number is the biggest success story weve had mrs 
king said at a press briefing we just have too a big a success 
on our hands the trick is how to manage it so that it works 
better 
mrs king said the agency is preparing television and newspaper 
public service announcements that encourage people to have 
breakfast with social security by calling between 7 am and 9 
am when the phone lines are less busy 
mrs king said a new study by the inspector generals office of 
