women reported such feelings 
the poll released tuesday also found men were less worried 
about chowing down and less conscious of dietary concerns 
fiftyseven percent of men said they were eating more fiber 
among women that rose to 70 percent fewer than four in 10 men 
sought more calcium six in ten women did 
overall 52 percent of the respondents said they were eating 
more oat bran which has been touted recently as an aid in lowering 
blood cholesterol again considerably fewer men than women said 
they had made the change 
