could result in irancontra prosecutors rejecting prospective 
jurors who otherwise would be favorable to the defense lawyers for 
reagans former national security adviser said 
they also said the testimony should be made public only after 
the jury in this case has been sworn and instructed regarding trial 
publicity 
alternatively poindexter asked that the media before the trial 
be provided only with a transcript of reagans testimony and that 
access to the videotape be deferred until the jury is sworn in 
in their own filing reagans lawyers asked that copies of the 
tape not be disseminated until the end of the trial and that 
public access to reagans testimony be limited to reviewing the 
videotape at a location under control of the court 
any earlier distribution of copies of the tape goes far beyond 
the requirements of the first amendment and may damage irreparably 
the rights of the defendant and the former president the former 
presidents lawyers argued 
