leon carter a black attorney representing jordan warned jurors 
not to let emotion overtake them 
there will be things in this trial that will inflame and 
excite you there will be fliers writings on the wall and other 
things that will get your emotions up carter said but once 
you have ridden that crest of emotion i ask you to look closely at 
the case and look to your reason and not emotion 
attorney general richard thornburgh said after the indictments 
were issued in september that prosecution of racial hate crimes is 
a priority of the justice department 
each of the federal charges carries up to 10 years in prison and 
a 250000 fine 
wood already has been sentenced to 10 years in prison and fined 
5000 by a state judge after admitting he sprayed swastikas and 
antisemitic slogans at the synagogue 
eleven other hammerskins associates were charged previously 
three out of five adults and four of six juveniles pleaded guilty 
