gold miners to stay illegally on yanomami indian lands and 
contributing to the genocide of the tribe 
deputy attorney general carlos mucci told a house session sarney 
and five cabinet ministers were permitting the devastation of the 
yanomamis the worlds largest primitive tribe and so were guilty 
of crimes of responsibility 
in an interview mucci said further the yanomamis situation 
is worse that what is reported the government is contributing to 
the quasigenocide 
despite protests by environmentalists sarney signed a decree on 
friday creating the uraricoera and catrimani mining areas in the 
northwestern jungle state of roraima near the venezuelan border 
the areas totaling about 1 million acres border the 
mineralrich yanomami reserves and are claimed by the tribe 
mucci head of a justice department committee on indian rights 
