confrontation 
sarney a civilian took office in 1985 ending 21 years of 
military rule he will be succeeded by presidentelect fernando 
collor de mello for a fiveyear term on march 15 
there is time for the legislature to adopt a position before 
march 15 it all depends on political will mucci said 
a clandestine gold rush to the yanomami territory began in 1987 
after government studies indicated a wealth of gold tin bauxite 
and diamonds on yanomami land 
since then the prospectors have destroyed rain forests chased 
off fish and game polluted rivers with mercury used in gold 
panning and spread venereal disease and tuberculosis among the 
peaceful tribe 
brazils roman catholic church says at least 1500 yanomamis of 
the 9000member tribe have died of malnutrition malaria and 
venereal diseases since the invasion began 
under international pressure the government last month 
announced a 4 million campaign to expel the prospectors by force 
if necessary 
but shortly after it offered the miners three tracts of virgin 
amazon rain forest near the reserve to avoid a bloodbath with the 
heavily armed miners 
