which once claimed 23 million acres of brazils northwestern amazon 
territory could be wiped out by further intrusions 
over the years the government carved up the yanomamis claim 
leaving them 19 scattered reservations totaling 5 million acres it 
declared the rest national parks and forests 
about 220000 native indians are left in brazil there were an 
estimated 5 million when the portuguese first landed here in 1500 
environmentalists say the miners will spill off into indian 
reservations in neighboring amazon states and decimate other tribes 
