from a peak of an estimated 290000 jews in 1975 dade county 
now is down to 225000 miami beach is down to 58000 of an 
overall city population of about 100000 from 82000 in 1982 
said sheskin who conducts random telephone surveys and counts 
traditional jewish names in city directories to track the 
population 
while there are varied reasons for the change a catalyst came 
in 1980 when cuban president fidel castro opened the port of 
mariel to people who wanted to leave 
among the 125000 cubans who came to this country were thousands 
of vagrants criminals and other misfits unwanted by castros 
revolution most of the marielitos headed to the miami area 
joining a halfmillion earlier cuban refugees some without 
relatives to join moved into south beach crowding into lowrent 
