<TEXT>
here is what has changed in 
apartheid and what remains in force 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
blacks allowed to form their own trade unions 
laws outlawing interracial marriage and sexual relations 
repealed 
the pass laws which required blacks in white areas to have 
a permit repealed 
influx control laws which restricted blacks freedom to move 
into urban areas abolished 
beaches theaters hotels restaurants and most forms of public 
transport desegegrated 
laws reserving for whites certain types of supervisory and 
technical jobs at mines repealed 
blacks given a policymaking role in provincial administration 
central business districts in major cities and towns opened to 
black traders 
blacks who previously could only rent homes now can obtain 
permanent ownership 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
black majority has no vote in national affairs blacks vote 
only in tribal homelands and local elections 
group areas act of 1950 mandates racial segregation of 
residential areas 
black land act of 1913 prevents blacks from owning property in 
the vast majority of the country 
population registration act of 1950 requires that all south 
africans be registered with the government by race without this 
act other apartheid laws would be difficult to enforce 
staterun schools segregated 
staterun hospitals and ambulance services segregated although 
exceptions made in emergencies and for specialized treatment 
separate amenities act of 1953 allows local officials to 
segregate facilities such as parks libraries and recreation 
centers the government says this law will be repealed this year 
only whites subject to military conscription 
parents cannot adopt children of other races 
</TEXT>
