<TEXT>
carol burnett may have come up with something 
new on television where recycling the past is usually the wave of 
the future 
in her anthology series for nbc carol amp company shell 
play a different character each week in what essentially are 
oneact comedies 
we put up a blank canvas every week and throw on the paint 
burnett said each story is characterdriven and focuses on 
relationships in essence its a pilot every week if someone 
said pick the most difficult form of television wed pick this 
thats why no ones ever done it before 
the show will be shot live in front of an audience featuring a 
repertory company and frequently a guest star burnett said 
each week we make a fresh start she said thats the 
challenge for the actors the writers the set designers 
everybody were even doing a musical 
nbc has not yet set a premiere date for the show but has said 
it will begin in late march 
matt williams who created abcs roseanne is the executive 
producer and head writer the repertory company is made up of terry 
kiser meagan fay richard kind jeremy piven and anita barone 
burnett of course starred for 12 years in the carol burnett 
show but that show like foxs the tracey ullman show 
relied on skits 
most anthologies in the past were dramatic there have been a 
few comedy anthologies 1985s george burns comedy week for 
instance but burns merely introduced a filmed show with a 
different cast each week 
as with her old variety show burnett will come out and meet the 
audience in the theater at the disney studio then shell change 
costumes and join the other actors the story will be acted out in 
sequence and at the end the actors will make a curtain call 
its important that the viewers see the audience she said 
we dont want anyone to think were using canned laughter ive 
only done a few things for television without an audience when i 
started this i said an audience was important especially if 
youre trying to be funny our players and guests are used to 
working before an audience 
that wasnt always true on her variety series where some of the 
guests were movie stars who had worked only before a camera gloria 
swanson who asked to take part after seeing burnetts famous spoof 
of sunset boulevard was very nervous and had to be coaxed 
through her songanddance role 
movie spoofs were a hallmark of burnetts old show an outgrowth 
of a childhood filled with countless hours in movie theaters 
recently she attended the american cinema awards 
i was in heaven burnett said every old movie star was 
there ann blyth huntz hall june allyson turhan bey it took 
almost an hour to introduce everybody people were just dying at 
seeing these people 
we havent done any spoofs yet on our new show she said 
but we did do a takeoff on the film noir detective films of the 
1940s the dick powell kind of thing in murder my sweet in which 
you spat out the dialogue like bullets we did it mainly to 
introduce our repertory company thats as close as weve gotten to 
a spoof were really doing stories 
in one show burnett plays the matriarch of a television soap 
opera who appears to be a terror until you see her with a security 
guard played by robert guillaume in another shes an eccentric 
woman who shows up on a dock in gulfport miss where nell carter 
is fishing her only concern is that shes going to be abducted by 
space aliens 
glenda jackson is a radio pop psychologist in another show in 
which burnett shows up at the station to say the psychologists 
advice ruined her life another spotlights a woman who surprises a 
few people when she goes to her high school reunion in yet 
another burnett and alex rocco play a romantic couple who continue 
to work together in a scientific laboratory 
burnett also has her own production company kalola productions 
at the disney studio in partnership with former television 
newswoman marcia brandwynne kalola is doing an interview show for 
the disney channel called a conversation with in which 
burnett so far has interviewed bob hope george burns and betty 
white 
kalola has a number of feature and television movies and a tv 
series in development with various branches of walt disney 
productions 
anna phelan hamilton who wrote mask and gorillas in the 
mist is writing a movie based on burnetts autobiography one 
more time a movie musical called rehearsal club is based on 
burnetts early life on broadway and a movie version of once 
upon a mattress the stage musical that made her a star is in 
the works 
im going to be like alfred hitchcock and have cameos in all 
these movies she said in once upon a mattress ill 
probably be the queen well have a big talent search for someone 
to play my old role as winifred 
</TEXT>
