<TEXT>
tom clancys hightech thrillers have been a phenomenon of the 
publishing industry although jammed with scientific data his 
novels have been bought by millions of readers despite their 
immense popularity and tense drama none has been dramatized on the 
screen until now 
thats understandable clancys labyrinthian plots and 
dependence on military hardware for suspense require the most deft 
of treatment on film the hunt for red october is fortunate in 
that regard it is a nailbiter from beginning to end 
like the book the film requires close attention the slightest 
blip on the sonar screen could mean destruction of a nuclear 
submarine the casual viewer should stay home 
red october named for the month of the russian revolution in 
1917 is the new soviet submarine one with fishlike gills that 
allows it to voyage undetected capt ramius sean connery heads 
the sub west on an unauthorized mission in the pregorbachev era 
both the soviet and us fleets mobilize to chase ramius the 
soviets realize he and his officers plan to defect the americans 
misinformed by moscow fear he is a maverick who might launch a 
nuclear attack on the united states 
cia agent jack ryan alec baldwin with experience in analyzing 
the soviet navy is enlisted to track down the red october aiding 
the pursuit is a los angelesclass nuclear sub commanded by scott 
glenn with a wizard sonar operator courtney b vance 
larry ferguson and donald stewart did a terrific job of 
compressing a huge novel into a playable screenplay john mctiernan 
proved with die hard that he can stretch suspense almost to the 
breaking point and he exceeds himself with the hunt for red 
october 
what a marvel sean connery is his dialogue is laconic but that 
great scottish face reveals everything in his mind alec baldwin 
makes the leap to stellar status with absolute ease kevin costner 
harrison ford and mel gibson make room for the new kid 
outstanding in the virtually allmale cast are glenn vance 
james earl jones sam neill richard jordan and peter firth 
mace neufeld as producer performed the almost superhuman task in 
putting together the multitude of details for the hunt for red 
october the paramount pictures release is rated pg for minor 
swearing and tension running time 125 minutes 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
motion picture association of america rating definitions 
g general audiences all ages admitted 
pg parental guidance suggested some material may not be 
suitable for children 
pg13 special parental guidance strongly suggested for 
children under 13 some material may be inappropriate for young 
children 
r restricted under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult 
guardian 
x no one under 17 admitted some states may have higher age 
restrictions 
