new york stories touchstone vhsbeta 8995 rated pg 
 
new york stories was a disaster during its theatrical 
release but it might play better on the small screen at home 
because you can always zoom to your favorite vignette and skip the 
others 
it began as an excellent idea take three top american 
filmmakers set them out on the streets of new york and loop their 
efforts into one fulllength feature to celebrate those collective 
talents and the city they supposedly enshrined 
unfortunately the idea doesnt quite gel the video consists of 
three vignettes by martin scorsese frances coppola and woody 
allen but only scorseses life lessons is worth the 8995 or 
cost of rental its also the first story in the production so you 
dont even need to touch the remote unless youre an unconditional 
woody allen fan skip the next two 
life lessons is the only vignette that truly mirrors the 
spirit and attitude of new york in this case the downtown art 
world it has a feel texture and mood thanks in part to the 
gritty and witty original screenplay by bronxborn writer richard 
price and the sensitive and probing lens of the celebrated 
cinematographer nestor almendros it is a tigheinrich 
thyssenbornemisza including works by 19 artists whose major 
painting are rare in this country including ernst ludwig kirchner 
emil nolde paul klee erich heckel and franz marc through march 
25 
