<TEXT>
many of bestselling novelist tony 
hillermans characters are scholars archaeologists professors 
curators and graduate assistants 
his central character navajo detective lt joe leaphorn has a 
degree in anthropology 
his lateset book coyote waits involves a train robbery and 
a feud between two professors of western history 
heres a bibilography of hillermans previous novels 
the blessing way 1970 leaphorn and a professor friend 
pursue a navajo witch 
the fly on the wall 1971 a novel of legislative intrigue 
dance hall of the dead 1973 leaphorn tracks a mysterious 
zuni dancer while following a trail of bodies hillerman won an 
edgar allen poe award from the mystery writers of america in 1974 
listening woman 1978 leaphorn goes up against a militant 
indian activist amid more murderous machinations 
people of darkness 1980 introduces officer jim chee a 
bright young detective who falls in love with a white woman and 
confronts a coldblooded killer 
the boy who made dragonfly 1980 a story for young people 
the dark wind 1982 to become the first of a series of 
motion pictures based on hillermans books chee and hopi deputy 
sheriff cowboy dashee solve some drugrelated murders 
the ghostway 1985 starts with murder at a shiprock car 
wash and leads chee to los angeles 
skinwalkers 1987 leaphorn and chee are united on a series 
of apparently witchrelated homicide cases 
a thief of time 1988 the leaphornchee tandem tackles 
artifact thievery an archaeologists disappearance and of course 
murder during an investigation that leads leaphorn to the 
artauction jungle of new york 
talking god 1989 a body dumped near the tracks sends 
leaphorn and chee off in apparently unrelated directions only to 
find theyre working on the same case in washington 
hillerman also has written or edited nonfiction books 
including the great taos bank robbery rio grande new 
mexico the spell of new mexico and indian country 
