<TEXT>
rising country music singer garth brooks 
says his songs are a piece of my heart 
the 27yearold singersongwriterguitarist has had two hit 
records with the first two songs released from his debut album 
garth brooks 
his if tomorrow never comes which was no 1 on the country 
music charts in december is about the need to tell loved ones that 
you love them 
his too young to feel this damn old about a rodeo 
contestant whose only friends are lonely women and bad booze was a 
hit record last summer 
you have to let your heart talk brooks said in an 
interview if you just let whats in your heart out you are 
true 
brooks a native of tulsa okla where he was the last of six 
children has had a rapid rise since moving to nashville in june 
1987 prior to that he was a student at oklahoma state university 
where he was a javelin thrower for the school track team 
he also sang with the group santa fe a regional band that 
performed throughout oklahoma texas and new mexico 
after relocating to nashville he took a job running a boot 
store he was able to earn a living while pushing his music career 
an arrangement some other aspiring singers do not have 
i got the managers job and got to hire one employee my 
wife he said i had a very fortunate start 
brooks whose stocky frame is usually capped off with a spiffy 
cowboy hat also began singing on songwriters demonstration tapes 
tapes of new unrecorded songs that composers play for record 
companies in hopes of getting them chosen for albums 
but his real break came when capitol records executives heard 
him perform at a nashville entertainment association showcase 
based on this performance he signed a recording contract with 
capitol 
brooks has joined a handful of other young singers who are 
apparently going to shape the country music sound of the 1990s 
you just pray that you are going to be one of the chosen ones 
still around in five 15 20 years he said 
he senses a change in country music themes a change that has 
earned his style of music a growing number of fans 
country music isnt my dad got run over at the truck wash 
right after my wife left me this morning the music is set in a 
manner that everybody can relate to not just the guy driving the 
truck its very real and people are turning to it its not 
stereotyped any more he said 
the music has got to be real i look for things the common man 
would say such as the guy at walmart real people today are going 
to walmart 
the cuts on his first album many of which he wrote or cowrote 
are touching tunes of emotion and lifes roadblocks 
the song cowboy bill is about a cowboy storyteller who 
thrilled kids with stories about his days as a texas ranger adults 
doubted his veracity until he was found dead with his badge 
the cut the dance is about the good times before losing a 
loved one 
in every time that it rains brooks sings about a romantic 
fling that loses its intensity the second time around 
