<TEXT>
four media companies today announced they are 
banding together to launch the first directtohome tv satellite 
service that will beam high definition television and digital sound 
on lowcost napkinsized dishes 
cablevision systems corp national broadcasting co news corp 
ltd and hughes communications inc signed a memorandum of 
understanding to create the first high power direct broadcast 
satellite service in 1993 
the companies plan to invest about 1 billion in the joint 
venture including up to onethird in equity and 325 million in 
nonrecourse debt 
the service called sky cable will use the most powerful 
space transmitter ever launched for commercial communications the 
companies said in a written statement 
the highpower satellite system will make as many as 108 new 
channels available through the use of digital video delivery beam 
high definition television and standard video signals and deliver 
digital quality audio 
reception will be made by a flat napkinsized dish that can be 
mounted on a windowsill or rooftop and purchased for about 300 at 
consumer electronics stores the companies said 
a conventional 10foot backyard satellite dish costs 
approximately 2000 to 3000 
the new service will give americans a taste of the next 
centurys boundless range of video choices sharply enhanced 
picture reception and more realistic sound said stephen j 
petrucci president and chief operating officer of general motors 
corps hughes communications unit which will provide the 
satellite system 
the companies said the new satellite venture likely would be the 
first to introduce hdtv to the united states on a broad consumer 
scale 
under the agreement the equity will be divided evenly among the 
partners and will be paid into the venture in equal amounts over 
the next four years the remaining funds will be financed as 
working capital 
charles f dolan chairman of cablevision systems corp said 
sky cable will give viewers in areas not served by cable many of 
whom dont have the space or funds for oldfashioned satellite 
dishes a less cumbersome and more economical way to get 
highquality reception and a variety of programming 
australias news corp owned by media magnate rupert murdoch 
currently uses direct broadcast satellite technology in its sky 
television system 
we expect to apply our experience to the development of sky 
cable murdoch said 
bob wright president of general electric cos nbc unit said 
that while free overtheair broadcasting will remain the heart 
of nbc the venture will help further the companys programming 
and hdtv goals 
this system capitalizes on our substantial investment in the 
development of an american high definition television system as it 
will provide an important means of delivering advanced tv to the 
home wright said 
local cable operators will be able to market sky cables 
services along with their own the companies said sky cable will 
provide subscribers with a choice of multichannel packages a la 
carte subscription channels and payperview programming 
sky cables programming also will be packaged for noncable 
homes and as a supplement for homes with wired cable 
