avon products inc said wednesday it plans to 
sell its remaining 60 percent stake in avon japan to a private 
japanese mail order company and its president in a cash deal valued 
at 450 million 
the big beauty products company decided to withdraw from japan 
after concluding that it would be too costly to try to prosper 
there an intensely competitive environment in which avon has had 
little success expanding its market share 
friends of freesia co ltd and freesia president veji sasaki 
will pay 408 million in cash at the closing 338 million plus 
70 million in advance royalties another 42 million in advance 
royalties will be paid 18 months later avon said 
the proposed deal which must be approved by avons board of 
directors provides for avon to receive 5 percent in royalties on 
all avon products sold by avon japan for the first 18 months after 
completion of the deal after a year and a half avon will receive 
3 percent in royalties 
avon which started the japan subsidiary about 20 years ago 
sold 40 percent of the company or 271 million shares on the open 
market in 1987 for 220 million 
avon chairman james e preston said proceeds from the sale of 
its remaining interest will be used to reduce its 600 million 
debt avon last year reduced its 11 billion debt by 500 million 
he said 
john cox avons spokesman said the company decided it would be 
too costly to continue trying to succeed in a highly competitive 
market where it has only about a 4 percent market share cox said 
avons assets could be put to better use in other pacific rim 
countries 
japan has a mature cosmetics market with strong competition 
cox said to grow would involve heavy investing in advertising 
marketing plant and equipment 
avon japan earned 153 million in fiscal 1989 on sales of 285 
million the subsidiary employs 2000 workers and has 350000 
independent sales representatives about 25 percent of its sales 
are by direct mail 
freesia a private company with sales of about 180 million 
will retain current avon management and operate the company as a 
subsidiary avon will give freesia exclusive use of its 
trademark intellectual property rights and product technology 
for 10 years 
avon also will retain two seats on the board of avon japan and 
will provide consulting and product research and development 
services 
avons board will consider the planned transaction at the next 
regular meeting scheduled for march 1 
securities analysts endorsed the sale plan and said it would 
improve the bottom line of the new yorkbased direct sales company 
andrew shore of shearson lehman hutton inc estimated the sale 
will contribute about 15 cents a share to avons 1990 earnings 
it will go a long way to restoring the health of the balance 
sheet 
the companys financial performance has been scrutinized over 
the past year or so by several investors contemplating possible 
takeovers avon rejected outright acquisition proposals of 21 
billion from rival direct sales company amway corp of ada mich 
and of 285 billion from minneapolisbased investor irwin jacobs 
it also fended off takeover feelers from mary kay cosmetics 
another leading direct seller of beauty products 
a limited partnership including a subsidiary of mary kay corp 
the dallasbased privately held parent of the cosmetics marketer 
also has been building a stake in avon stock chartwell associates 
announced in late december that it had increased its holding to 87 
percent 
avon last week said it earned 546 million or 34 cents a 
share in 1989 compared with a deficit of 4045 million or 679 
a share in 1988 the 1988 results reflected 546 million in losses 
from discontinued operations sales in 1989 rose 8 percent to 33 
billion from 1988s 31 billion 
