jaguar plc the luxury british automaker dogged 
by an image of slipshod quality is recalling nearly twothirds of 
the cars it has sold in the united states since 1988 because of 
potential brake problems 
the 38315 models affected contain a highpressure hose that 
could rupture and spurt hot brake fluid onto an engine causing 
smoke fire and loss of braking power the automaker said the 
brake recall also affects 56000 jaguars sold in other countries 
in addition jaguar said it is recalling 38385 cars sold in 
this country dating to 1979 for defects that could cause the 
automatic cruise control device to jam raising the risk of crashes 
the company said it is unaware of any accidents or injuries that 
may have resulted from these defects which will be repaired free 
of charge owners will be notified by mail 
the recalls come at a particularly awkward time for jaguar 
which is suffering from a protracted slide in sales in its most 
important foreign market the united states just as japanese and 
german competitors are becoming more aggressive about selling 
luxury cars in this country 
the british company which recently agreed to be acquired by 
ford motor co has long been tainted by reputation for 
inconsistent quality temperamental cars and customer complaints 
about service 
in the brake recall dealerships will check the brake systems of 
all xj6 vanden plas and majestic cars sold in the united states 
for potential leaks the cruise control recall affects 1979 model 
xj12 sedans and 1982 to 1990 model xjs cars 
