<TEXT>
for allen i questrom its almost like going 
back home again to rescue the family from crisis 
questrom spent 23 years with federated department stores but 
quit when it was acquired by campeau corp of canada nearly two 
years ago with billions of dollars in borrowed money 
at the time he feared such an enormous amount of debt would 
force federated to drastically change its philosophy away from 
quality and more toward highvolume selling and priceslashing 
promotions not his way of running a retailer profitably 
now questrom is in charge of resurrecting federated and another 
of campeaus multibillion dollar debtfinanced acquisitions allied 
stores corp which both sought protection from creditors last 
month in the biggest retailing bankruptcy filing in history 
questrom has minimized his contact with the press since he took 
over feb 2 as chairman and chief executive of federated and 
allied but at a news conference to announce his new job he 
laughed when asked whether he thought the task ahead would be the 
biggest of his career 
yes i think thats safe to say he said 
his new boss federated stores inc chairman and chief executive 
officer g william miller was more direct 
if you hadnt said that i would have gotten out of here 
said miller a former us treasury secretary 
questrom 49 was hired away from neimanmarcus a 22store 
specialty chain based in dallas as an added inducement to help 
lead the rescue he will be paid 12 million a year although 
questrom has insisted thats not the reason he came back 
widely respected in the retail business questrom is known as a 
believer in oldfashioned fundamentals clean stores quality 
service merchandise appropriate to a shoppers income level in 
his view a store that sells 700 womens dresses for example 
should not be peddling 19 shoes 
questrom clearly faces an enormous problem because he will have 
to combine his philosophy with a strategy that produces more 
revenue cuts costs satisfies the bankruptcy court and appeases 
anxious creditors 
the massachusetts native began his tenure with federated in 1965 
as an executive trainee at the abraham amp straus chain and by 1973 
had become a merchandise manager later he ran both richs and 
