filing for reorganization to concentrate more on their core 
businesses 
we are a department store company now we were before a kind 
of a broadbased retail company i believe the talents of the 
organization now are much more focused questrom said 
really its for jim and i and the company to really just put 
the priorities in order and to focus our attention on running the 
business to benefit our customers and i think we can do it he 
said 
questrom said the reorganizations under chapter 11 of the 
federal bankruptcy laws give federated and allied one advantage in 
luring merchandise suppliers the supervision of the us 
bankruptcy court means companies that deal with federated and 
allied now receive first priority for payment over creditors who 
dealt with federated and allied before their jan 15 filings 
from a retail point of view or a vendor point of view this is 
the safest company to ship to today this is the place to be 
shipping in terms of making sure you get your payments questrom 
said 
a more natural advantage the company has is its geographical 
reach in some of the most important us metropolitan markets 
we own the major properties in each of those cities he 
said i think our competitive position will in fact come back 
to normal in the next 30 to 45 days 
