<TEXT>
a former general partner of kohlberg kravis 
roberts amp co who sued the cofounders of the leveraged buyout firm 
in a highstakes dispute over money has settled out of court for an 
undisclosed amount 
a document filed in a new york state supreme court feb 7 shows 
jerome kohlbergs claims against the company and the other 
partners henry r kravis and george b roberts have been 
discontinued with prejudice and without cost to either party 
the phrase with prejudice means those claims cannot be 
raised in any future lawsuit nonetheless the documents language 
suggests kohlberg could bring claims that may arise from the future 
conduct of the defendants 
the terms of the settlement evidently also require both sides 
not to talk about the matter publicly they declined to comment or 
even confirm a settlement had been reached 
the quiet resolution of this legal brawl came less than six 
months after kohlberg a pioneer in the business of debtfinanced 
takeovers known as leveraged buyouts slapped his expartners with 
the lawsuit 
he claimed the firm reduced his stake in several companies 
acquired while he was one of kkrs general partners kohlberg 
claims that violated an agreement he made with the firm when he 
left its management in 1987 the defendants denied the claim 
kkr is the leader in arranging leveraged buyouts in which 
companies are acquired with borrowed money repaid with their 
earnings sale of assets or a combination of both kkr holds the 
record for the biggest takeover in history the 25 billion 
leveraged buyout of rjr nabisco inc 
the firms operations a mystery to the public have made its 
partners enormously wealthy but some of the most recent deals have 
run into trouble because of difficulties in repaying or 
renegotiating debt 
kohlberg kravis and roberts formed their partnership in 1976 
with each serving as general partners who managed the firm and 
directed its acquisitions and investments 
kohlberg remained a general partner until 1987 when after a 
fallingout with kravis and roberts over the firms strategy he 
became a limited partner sharing in kohlberg kravis profits but 
not in its management 
among the deals undertaken while kohlberg was a general partner 
were the 1986 leveraged buyouts of consumer products company 
beatrice cos for 61 billion and the grocery chain safeway stores 
inc for 42 billion 
</TEXT>
